result.execSummary:
The defendant David J Tallier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

The defendant may not consume/possess any alcohol.

The defendant may not enter into any taverns/bars.
Submit DNA sample if one has not been previously submitted.

The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must attend at least one NA or similar treatment program each week and provide proof of attendance to P&P. 

The defendant must follow thru will all treatment plans from previous treatment.

Huber allowed.

Eligible for community service under 973.20.

records.addlTxt: Defendant David J Tallier in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Jodie Bednar-Clemens  appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:53 PM. Scholke provides court with plea questionnaire as the matter is resolved. Bednar - amend count #1 to possession of meth contrary to 961.41(3g)(g) - class I felony - plead to amended count - DRI #2 - joint recommendation of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 2 years  with conditions of: 30 days in FC jail, costs, AODA assessment and follow thru, absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, employment/school, take all medications as prescribed and in the manner in whch they are prescribed, no possession of any illegal substances. Scholke and Tallier agree. Court dismisses and reads in count #2. Court amends count #1 to possession of meth contrary to 961.41(3g)(g) - reads new penalties. Tallier pleads NC to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Scholke makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Tallier withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - impose 3.5 years in WI State Prison System, consisiting of 1.5 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES, stayed, place on probation for 2 years with conditions of: 30 days in FC jail - huber allowed - eligible for community service under 973.20 - report by 8:30 AM on 7/31/15 - Scholke will research credit due within 5 days thru stip and order if possible, costs with surcharges - paid thru probation, AODA and follow thru, follow thru with all treatment plans from previous treatment, attend at least one NA or similar treatment program each week and provide proof of attendance to P&P, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars,  submit DNA sample unless already given, no voting rights, no possession of firearms, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant David J Tallier in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 2:04 pm. Scholke indicates no resolution and asks for JT date. Bond continued.  Jury trial scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant David J Tallier in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 8:53 AM. Scholke - not resolved - only had full discovery for less than 48 hours. Court continues bond, will set for another FPT.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 29, 2015 at 04:00 pm.

Defendant David J Tallier in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:15 PM. Scholke wants to proceed to PH. State calls Deputy Thomas Robinson. Robinson sworn in at 3:16 PM. Direct exam by State. Record reflects proper identification of the defendant. Cross exam by Scholke at 3:25 PM. Court asks question of witness. Robinson excused at 3:30 PM. State calls Lindsey Collins. Court does collaquey with the witness regarding her 5th amendment rights. Collins does not waive her 5th amendment rights. State - did make an agreement with the defendant in her case in regards to testifying today. Collins understands, will waive her 5th amendment rights. Court finds the defendant has waived her 5th amendment rights. Direct exam by State at 3:33 PM. Record reflects identification of the defendant by this witness. Cross exam by Scholke at 3:39 PM. State objects - relevance - sustained (3:41 PM). Court questions witness at 3:42 PM. Re-direct by State at 3:42 PM. Collins excused at 3:42 PM. Court finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State files Information that mirrors complaint. Scholke has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond and sets for FPT.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 22, 2015 at 09:00 am.
